 "coaching": {
  "headline": "A clean objective win — 87k–19k on objectives and 6–1 in the fights around them, even with the carry lane on the back foot.",
  "team": "You won the map, not the lanes. Objective damage was 87k to 19k and you took the objective fights 6–1, despite Cuban's Sparrow being down in lane to Murdock ('theirs all game', lost first tower). Mr_Meat31's The Fey (5/3/10, team-high 27.8k) and Goldilocks' Iggy (7/4/8, 28k) were the engines, Xeebs' Khaimera anchored 34k objective damage, and Willy's Steel chipped in 12 assists. Keep snowballing objectives off your mid/offlane tempo.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "Objective tempo beat lane parity — you turned a losing carry lane into a win by grouping for objectives (87k–19k). Same plan next time.",
  "perPlayer": {
   "7c8ab99c-31c5-4ea5-a6fa-e0d6417c3f1b": "The Fey mid, 5/3/10 and team-high 27.8k damage — your pocket mid carried again. Your career stat rates offlane as your best role, but The Fey mid keeps over-delivering; worth treating as a real main.",
   "16f28434-561f-4f23-9454-40321f4a1ef3": "Iggy offlane, 7/4/8 with 28k damage and 25k into objectives — exactly the tempo offlaner this comp wanted. Clean game.",
   "a412baf3-dd17-4f89-8ecf-9d0704f3a79e": "Khaimera jungle, 8/6/5 and team-high 34k objective damage — you anchored the macro lead. Build note: you skipped armor (Basilisk/Overlord) into a 4-physical enemy comp; pick it up when you see that draft.",
   "a0c393cc-1437-4bdc-8168-64676ce2166c": "Sparrow into Murdock was an uphill lane ('theirs all game', first tower lost) and 4/3/3 is a fine hold — but your core was off-meta (no Storm Breaker/Sky Splitter/Spectra); the standard core spikes harder and would've turned the lane.",
   "10edbf65-457d-48d0-9151-9df5b4fcb40a": "Steel support, 2/4/12 — 12 assists is real enabling and it worked. Still, Steel isn't your edge: your Belica (56%) and Zinx (56%) give the team more than a 15.7k tank support."
  }
 },
